				</div>
                				<h4><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/09/19/a-soaring-debut-for-alibaba/?ref=dealbook">A Soaring Debut for Alibaba</a></h4>
				<p class="nyt-article-byline">By MICHAEL J. DE LA MERCED</p>
				<p class="nyt-article-summary">The Chinese Internet giant, which raised $21.8 billion in its stock sale, instantly became one of the biggest publicly traded technology companies in the world.</p>
			</div>
			</p>
<div id="addendums" class="addendums"><div class="story-addendum theme-correction"><strong>Correction: September 23, 2014</strong> <br>An earlier version of this column misstated when Jack Ma first visited the United States. It was 1995, not 1999. </div></div>	</div>
